description: Burn After Reading is a 2008 black comedy film written, produced and directed by Joel and Ethan Coen[1]. The film stars John Malkovich, George Clooney, Tilda Swinton, Frances McDormand and Brad Pitt. It was released in the USA on September 12, 2008 and it was released on October 17, 2008 in the UK. The film had its premiere on August 27, 2008 when it opened the 2008 Venice Film Festival.[2] The film is the brothers&#039; first to follow their Academy Award winning Best Picture, No Country for Old Men.
